<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!DOCTYPE rpl PUBLIC "-//ROCKLYTE//DTD RPL 1.0//EN">

<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
   <defs>
      <image id="add" xlink:href="icons:items/add" width="64" height="64"/>
      <image id="cancel" xlink:href="icons:items/cancel" width="32" height="32"/>
   </defs>
</svg>

<body face="Noto Sans" font-size="10pt" margins="24"/>

<page name="Index">
   <h1>Floating Widget Benchmark</h1>

   <p>Before the first floating widget there is a normal run of text that should establish the current line and margin
   state correctly. <image align="right" src="url(#add)" width="64" height="64" padding="8 0 12 12"/> After the
   floating widget is placed, the following text must wrap around the occupied clip region rather than overlap it.
   Donec sed ligula vel risus pellentesque placerat. Vestibulum ante ipsum primis in faucibus orci luctus et ultrices
   posuere cubilia curae; Donec sit amet luctus ipsum. Suspendisse porttitor tristique mauris.</p>

   <p>This paragraph uses a centred floating widget. <image align="center" src="url(#cancel)" width="48" height="48"
   padding="10 0 10 0"/> The text on either side should interact with the clip region and continue wrapping naturally
   after the occupied space has been traversed. Integer sodales ante at risus ullamcorper, ut luctus tortor feugiat.
   Cras ut lectus eu turpis imperdiet pulvinar. Nulla facilisi. Sed feugiat varius suscipit.</p>

   <p>The final paragraph mixes inline and floating widgets together: start_<image src="url(#cancel)"/>_end and then a
   right-aligned floating image follows. <image align="right" src="url(#cancel)" width="40" height="40" padding="8 0
   8 10"/> Morbi in viverra felis. Maecenas ultrices est non metus faucibus, vitae tincidunt ipsum interdum. Aenean
   congue volutpat erat, a tristique sem dapibus quis.</p>
</page>
